01/09/2006
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia -- UNMIK on Thursday (31 August) formally transferred all transport services provided especially for Kosovo's minorities to the government in Pristina. 
UNMIK official Patricia Waring said she is confident the Kosovo authorities would fulfill their commitments to ensure freedom of movement, including a train from Leposavic to Skopje as well as a number of bus services. 
The transfer of authority is part of Kosovo's efforts to meet international standards. 
(UN Press Release - 01/09/06)
